If an Iterable is not a collection, we're returning the opposite of what we should. Is currently:

``` java
  private static boolean isEmpty(Iterable<?> iterable) {
    return iterable instanceof Collection
        ? ((Collection<?>) iterable).isEmpty()
        : iterable.iterator().hasNext();
  }
```

Should be:

``` java
  private static boolean isEmpty(Iterable<?> iterable) {
    return iterable instanceof Collection
        ? ((Collection<?>) iterable).isEmpty()
        : !iterable.iterator().hasNext();
  }
```

Or we could just use Iterables.isEmpty().

